<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
              xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
              Foreground="#E0E0E0"
              Background="#1E1F22"
              FontFamily="Segoe UI"
              FontSize="14"
              PagePadding="32,24,32,24">

    <Paragraph FontSize="28" FontWeight="Bold" Foreground="#FFD700" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Roofs: Walkables &amp; RF4 Tiles
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Foreground="#A0A0A0" FontSize="13" Margin="0,0,0,16">
        Adding, editing, and managing walkable containers and roof tiles.
    </Paragraph>
    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,0,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,4,0,4">
        Viewing Walkables
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Walkables appear as numbered circles on the <Bold>Walkable layer</Bold> (toggle with the
        layer button in the toolbar). They are also listed in the <Bold>Walkables panel</Bold> on
        the right side of the Roofs tab.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        Each walkable entry shows:
    </Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="16,4,0,0" Foreground="#E0E0E0">
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                <Bold>Walkable ID</Bold> (e.g., Walkable #3)
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                <Bold>Building ID</Bold> it's attached to
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                <Bold>Bounding box</Bold> (X1, Z1 → X2, Z2)
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                <Bold>Height</Bold> in quarter storeys
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                <Bold>RF4 count</Bold> — how many roof tiles it contains
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
    </List>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,4">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMapEditor;component/Help/Images/roofs_walkables_list.png"
               MaxWidth="700" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>
    <Paragraph Foreground="#888888" FontSize="11" FontStyle="Italic" Margin="0,0,0,8" TextAlignment="Center">
        Screenshot: Walkables panel showing list of walkables with IDs, building IDs, bounds, heights, and RF4 counts
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Adding a New Walkable
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        You can add a new walkable to a building even if it already has existing walkables. This
        is useful for creating overlapping walkable regions at different heights (e.g., a raised
        platform on a rooftop).
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9ECBFF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Step-by-Step
    </Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Decimal" Margin="16,6,0,6" Foreground="#E0E0E0">
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                Select a building from the building filter dropdown (or use the building already
                selected from the Buildings tab).
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                Click the <Bold>Add button</Bold> next to the Walkables panel.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                On the map canvas, <Bold>click and drag</Bold> to define the walkable area.
                An <Bold>orange box</Bold> highlights the region as you drag.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                Release the mouse button. The <Bold>Add Walkable Region</Bold> dialog appears.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                Set the <Bold>Height</Bold> in quarter storeys (e.g., 8 for 2 storeys high).
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                Click <Bold>Add Walkable</Bold>. The walkable is created and appears in the list.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
    </List>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,4,0,4">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMapEditor;component/Help/Images/roofs_add_walkable.png"
               MaxWidth="700" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>
    <Paragraph Foreground="#888888" FontSize="11" FontStyle="Italic" Margin="0,0,0,8" TextAlignment="Center">
        Screenshot: Add Walkable Region dialog showing height input and Add Walkable button, with orange box preview on canvas
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Editing an Existing Walkable
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        You can edit a walkable's height. The bounding box cannot be changed without deleting and
        recreating the walkable.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9ECBFF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Step-by-Step
    </Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Decimal" Margin="16,6,0,6" Foreground="#E0E0E0">
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                <Bold>Double-click</Bold> the walkable in the Walkables list, OR
                <Bold>double-click</Bold> the numbered circle on the Walkable layer on the map canvas.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                The <Bold>Walkable Preview</Bold> window appears showing the walkable's properties.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                Change the <Bold>Height</Bold> value (in quarter storeys).
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                Click <Bold>Apply</Bold> to commit the height change.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
    </List>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,4,0,4">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMapEditor;component/Help/Images/roofs_edit_walkable.png"
               MaxWidth="700" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>
    <Paragraph Foreground="#888888" FontSize="11" FontStyle="Italic" Margin="0,0,0,8" TextAlignment="Center">
        Screenshot: Walkable Preview window showing walkable properties (bounds, height) with Apply button
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Deleting a Walkable
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Deleting a walkable removes it and <Bold>all RF4 tiles it contains</Bold>. This is a
        destructive operation.
    </Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Decimal" Margin="16,6,0,6" Foreground="#E0E0E0">
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                Select the walkable from the Walkables list.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                Click the <Bold>Delete</Bold> button, or press the <Bold>Delete</Bold> key.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                Confirm the deletion in the dialog that appears.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
    </List>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Adding Roof Tiles (RF4)
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Roof tiles are typically added to <Bold>warehouse buildings</Bold> (for floors) or
        <Bold>houses with sloped roofs</Bold>. Roof tiles must be added to an existing walkable
        container.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9ECBFF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Step-by-Step
    </Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Decimal" Margin="16,6,0,6" Foreground="#E0E0E0">
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                Select the <Bold>desired walkable</Bold> from the Walkables list that should
                contain the roof tiles.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                Click the <Bold>Add button</Bold> next to the Roof Tiles panel. The
                <Bold>Add Roof Face to Walkable</Bold> window appears.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                You have two options:
            </Paragraph>
            <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="16,2,0,0" Foreground="#E0E0E0">
                <ListItem>
                    <Paragraph>
                        <Bold>Fill Entire Walkable</Bold> — Creates a flat roof tile for every cell
                        in the walkable's bounding box
                    </Paragraph>
                </ListItem>
                <ListItem>
                    <Paragraph>
                        <Bold>Add Single Tile</Bold> — Adds one roof tile at a specific X, Z position
                    </Paragraph>
                </ListItem>
            </List>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                Set the <Bold>Height</Bold> in quarter storeys. It should automatically match the
                walkable's height, but you can adjust it.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                Click <Bold>Add Flat Roof</Bold> to fill the walkable, or <Bold>Add Tile</Bold>
                to add a single tile.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
    </List>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,4,0,4">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMapEditor;component/Help/Images/roofs_add_rf4.png"
               MaxWidth="700" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>
    <Paragraph Foreground="#888888" FontSize="11" FontStyle="Italic" Margin="0,0,0,8" TextAlignment="Center">
        Screenshot: Add Roof Face to Walkable window with Fill Entire Walkable / Add Single Tile options, height input, and buttons
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Editing Roof Tiles
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Editing individual roof tiles allows you to create <Bold>sloped roofs</Bold> by adjusting
        corner heights.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9ECBFF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Opening the Roof Tile Editor
    </Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Decimal" Margin="16,6,0,6" Foreground="#E0E0E0">
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                <Bold>Double-click</Bold> a roof tile on the <Bold>Roof Tiles layer</Bold> on the
                map canvas, OR
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                <Bold>Double-click</Bold> a roof tile entry in the <Bold>Roof Face 4 Entries</Bold>
                panel (shown when a walkable is selected).
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
    </List>
    <Paragraph>
        The <Bold>Roof Tile Editor</Bold> window appears with three sections:
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9ECBFF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Roof Tile Properties Section
    </Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="16,4,0,0" Foreground="#E0E0E0">
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                <Bold>X and Z Coordinate</Bold> — Position of the tile on the map (read-only)
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                <Bold>SE Corner Height</Bold> — The base height of the cell in quarter storeys.
                This is the primary height value.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                <Bold>NW, NE, SW Corner Offsets</Bold> — Height deltas in <Bold>pixels</Bold>
                (not quarter storeys). Negative values create downward slopes; positive values
                create upward slopes.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                <Bold>Roof Direction Checkbox</Bold> — Indicates which way the tile splits diagonally.
                A preview box shows the split direction visually.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                <Bold>Special Marker</Bold> — Usually always set for roof tiles. Exact purpose
                unclear; leave it checked.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
    </List>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9ECBFF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        RF4 Draw Flags Section
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        These flags do not appear to be used by the editor or engine, or they are populated
        procedurally during gameplay. You can generally ignore this section.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9ECBFF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Applying Changes
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        After setting the corner heights and properties, you have three application options:
    </Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="16,4,0,0" Foreground="#E0E0E0">
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                <Bold>Apply to Single Tile</Bold> — Updates only the current tile
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                <Bold>Apply to All Tiles</Bold> — Updates every RF4 tile in the walkable with the
                same corner height values
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                <Bold>Apply to Selection</Bold> — Opens a selection tool; click and drag on the
                map canvas to select a rectangular area of tiles to apply the properties to
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
    </List>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,4">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMapEditor;component/Help/Images/roofs_rf4_editor.png"
               MaxWidth="700" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>
    <Paragraph Foreground="#888888" FontSize="11" FontStyle="Italic" Margin="0,0,0,8" TextAlignment="Center">
        Screenshot: Roof Tile Editor window showing position, SE/NW/NE/SW corner heights, roof direction checkbox with preview, special marker, and Apply buttons
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Deleting Roof Tiles
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        To delete individual roof tiles:
    </Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Decimal" Margin="16,6,0,6" Foreground="#E0E0E0">
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                Select a walkable to view its RF4 tiles in the Roof Face 4 Entries panel.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                Select the tile(s) you want to delete from the list.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                Click the <Bold>Delete</Bold> button or press the <Bold>Delete</Bold> key.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
    </List>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Tips
    </Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="16,4,0,0" Foreground="#E0E0E0">
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                Use <Bold>Fill Entire Walkable</Bold> when creating flat warehouse floors or flat
                rooftops. This creates RF4 tiles across the entire bounding box automatically.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                For <Bold>sloped roofs</Bold>, first fill the walkable, then edit individual tiles
                (or use Apply to Selection) to set corner height offsets.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                Corner height offsets are in <Bold>pixels</Bold>, not quarter storeys. 1 QS = 64 pixels,
                so a typical slope might use offsets of -32, -64, etc.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                The <Bold>Apply to Selection</Bold> button is very useful for creating sloped roofs
                on one side of a building without affecting the other sides.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                When the Walkable layer is visible, numbered circles on the map make it easy to
                quickly identify and select walkables for editing.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
    </List>

</FlowDocument>
